22/12/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The chief Croatian negotiator with the EU in talks on the Free Movement of Capital chapter, Vladimir Drobnjak, said on Wednesday (21 December) that Croatia has undertaken no obligations concerning the opening of its real estate market to foreigners. The issue is sensitive, particularly in the light of recent criticism by Italy that Zagreb discriminates against Italian citizens trying to buy property. 
Also Wednesday, the defence ministry announced that General Dragutin Repinc, 46, has been picked to head the UN team of military observers in Kashmir. Croatia has seven officers there, monitoring the peace agreement between India and Pakistan. (Novi list - 22/12/05; HRT, APP - 21/12/05)
